  "page": null,
  "source": "[\\set.theoretic.cartesian.product:of{A}:and{B}]\nDefines: P is \\set\nwhen: A, B is \\set\nexpresses:\n. forAll: z is \\set\n  then:\n  . have:\n    . exists: a, b is \\set\n      suchThat:\n      . a \"in\" A\n      . b \"in\" B\n      . z = \\set.theoretic.ordered.pair:of{a}:and{b}\n    iff: z \"in\" P\nDocumented:\n. called: \"cartesian product of $A?$ and $B?$\"\n. written: \"A? \\times B?\"\n. description: \"The cartesian product $A \\times B = \\{z \\in \\mathcal{P}(\\mathcal{P}(A \\cup B)) \\mid z = (a, b) \\text{ for some } a \\in A, b \\in B\\}$, the set of all ordered pairs $(a, b)$ with $a \\in A$ and $b \\in B$.\"\nId: \"64578792-cf4f-4497-9c79-3fc0189a08e4\"",
